{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Stage-2 bounded LLM pairwise overlap judge (advisory findings + suggested link commands)\n\n## Why\nPrecision lives in stage 2, not in a similarity threshold. The recall spike (epic experiment comment) showed retrieval recall is excellent BUT flagged precision-at-scale as the residual risk (same model produces query+doc digests ‚Üí vocabularies converge ‚Üí near-duplicates converge too). This judge IS that precision mitigation: a bounded LLM pairwise classifier over the ~K stage-1 candidates.\n\n## What ‚ÄĒ output schema (fully specified)\nOutput `overlap_verdict` (register in `contracts.py`): `{relation: enum, shared_artifact: string|null, confidence: number, abstain: bool}`, `relation ‚ąą {duplicates, supersedes, depends_on, related_distinct, unrelated}` (CLOSED). Only `duplicates|supersedes|depends_on` are surfaceable; the `rebar link` relation set is the 6 built-ins (`blocks, depends_on, relates_to, duplicates, supersedes, discovered_from`) ‚ÄĒ the judge only ever emits the three surfaceable ones.\n- Both orderings (A‚ÜíB, B‚ÜíA). AGGREGATION: surface ONLY if both orderings agree on the SAME surfaceable relation AND each cites a non-null `shared_artifact` AND both `confidence >= overlap_conf_threshold`; else downgrade to `related_distinct` (not surfaced). Position-bias disagreement fails safe toward \"distinct.\" An LLM-emitted `abstain: true` in EITHER ordering also downgrades (not surfaced) and does not consume a surface slot. (No single-ordering cascade ‚ÄĒ it would reintroduce the position bias the dual-ordering rule removes.)\n- Surface ‚Č§ `overlap_surface_cap` (default 3) highest-confidence results: `{counterpart_id, relation, shared_artifact, confidence, link_command}`, `link_command = \"rebar link <query> <counterpart> <relation>\"`.\n- K candidates ‚Üí 2K judge calls (both orderings), flat in corpus size.\n- Errors: LLM timeout/error/malformed output on a candidate ‚Üí treated as `abstain` (dropped), logged; never raises to the caller.\n\n## Config (LLMConfig, not VerifyConfig)\n`overlap_conf_threshold` (default 0.7), `overlap_surface_cap` (default 3) on `LLMConfig` (`src/rebar/llm/config.py`, `[tool.rebar.llm]`, `REBAR_LLM_OVERLAP_*`) ‚ÄĒ LLM tunables; `_config_schema.py` reserves `llm.*`, so NOT `VerifyConfig`.\n\n## Dependencies\nS5 (`OverlapCandidate` interface + query/corpus digests). Consumed by S7. (S5 is a sibling story; a codebase grep won't find `OverlapCandidate` until it lands.)\n\n## Scope\n- New `src/rebar/llm/overlap/judge.py` + rubric prompt `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/overlap_judge.md` (`execution_mode: single_turn`, `outputs: overlap_verdict`, `category: overlap`) whose body MUST encode: the 4-way classification, the require-a-cited-shared-artifact gate, the both-orderings instruction, and the abstain-when-unsure criterion.\n- `overlap_verdict` schema `src/rebar/schemas/overlap_verdict.schema.json` + `register_contract(\"overlap_verdict\", <builder>)`; config keys on `LLMConfig`.\n- OUT: retrieval (S5), wiring (S7).\n\n## Testing\n- `tests/unit/test_overlap_judge.py` (FakeRunner): `test_agree` (both agree+artifact ‚Üí surfaced); `test_disagree_downgrade`; `test_requires_artifact` (null artifact ‚Üí not surfaced); `test_abstain_dropped` (no slot consumed); `test_cap` (‚Č§ surface_cap); `test_link_command` (valid relation); `test_llm_error_abstain` (no raise).\n- Precision/recall check as a PYTEST FIXTURE test (NOT the prompt-eval harness ‚ÄĒ no registered scorer exists for the `overlap_verdict` shape): `test_judge_precision_recall` over a LABELED fixture of ‚Č•12 pairs (`tests/fixtures/overlap_pairs/`, format documented) computes precision AND recall and asserts precision ‚Č•0.8 AND recall ‚Č•0.6 (the recall floor stops an abstain-everything judge from trivially passing). Proving command: `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_overlap_judge.py::test_judge_precision_recall`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Judges both orderings, aggregates by the stated rule; `pytest ...::{test_agree,test_disagree_downgrade}`.\n- [ ] Surfaces only with a non-null `shared_artifact`, else `related_distinct`; `::test_requires_artifact`. Abstain drops without consuming a slot; `::test_abstain_dropped`.\n- [ ] ‚Č§ `overlap_surface_cap` (default 3) findings, each `{counterpart_id, relation‚ąą{duplicates,supersedes,depends_on}, shared_artifact, confidence, link_command}`; `link_command` valid; `::{test_cap,test_link_command}`.\n- [ ] LLM error on a candidate ‚Üí abstain, logged, no raise; `::test_llm_error_abstain`.\n- [ ] Fixture test `test_judge_precision_recall` (‚Č•12 labeled pairs) asserts precision ‚Č•0.8 AND recall ‚Č•0.6; `overlap_conf_threshold` (0.7)/`overlap_surface_cap` (3) configurable on `LLMConfig`.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783625648765808001,"uuid":"253f2ce3-068f-46a0-85bd-cfc3eef781a6"}